(DECnet Phase IV had 24-bit addressing—fatal for internet scale.) show newline
(Cyberspace is designed for IPv6: 128-bit addresses, global mesh, same) show newline
(security principles.) show newline
() show newline
(The NSA Zero Trust framework \(January 2026\) independently validates the) show newline
(capability approach. Their seven pillars—User, Device, Network,) show newline
(Application, Data, Visibility, Automation—map directly to our) show newline
(architecture: identity via SPKI principals, device attestation) show newline
(\(Memo-046\), capability-constrained routing, per-operation authorization.) show newline
("Never trust, always verify" is axiom A1 restated. "Assume breach" is) show newline
(why we use content-addressing and cryptographic binding rather than) show newline
(perimeter trust.) show newline
